# Citizen science and gamification using digital platform to crowdsource solutions

![](data:image/png;base64,)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Overview
Citizen Science and gamification using digital platforms to crowdsource solutions is a tool that leverages citizen engagement and gamification features to encourage innovators to share ideas and solutions.

## Purpose
This method is used to collect ideas and solutions from various parts of the country, serving as an interactive database for policymakers to validate annual development plan progress.

## How it works
The platform identifies ideas and solutions without requiring field visits every time. It encourages inclusiveness, stakeholder engagement, and local government participation to map local solutions and upload them on the platform.

## Requirements
Inclusiveness is key, with all stakeholders engaged from the beginning in prototyping and user testing. Local governments' engagement and champions at the local level are critical for mapping local solutions.

## Reflections
The platform must be agile and adaptive to changing situations and needs.

## Examples
Argentina's UNDP AccLab, Co Lab, together with the Ministry of Science, Technology and Innovation (MINCYT), co-created a mapping of national citizen science environmental initiatives.
